choices.text: to keep my walker rolling fast enough for me to make it on before the bus is full. This can be annoying for others. But, this morning, I am so frustrated and angry. First, I make it on the bus and I settle into a window seat. I have to get by two people to sit down so that feels bad. You would think that they’d both get up for me, but they don’t, they just hover and when finally someone does get up and I pass, they watch as I put my things down and get comfy. To me, this is rude. You should help someone in that situation. And then when I arrive in the city centre for my 9:30 exam (that I showed up to the exact moment it happened), there was a construction crew building an entire new shop right smack in front of the school. So, I had to find my way around while they screamed and made me scream at the very least. They’d also brought in a huge electronic saw. I just couldn’t take it so when I got to the other end of the building, I am so close to tears. There was nobody around in the empty building and I started sobbing. Wait a second while I tell my students that crying is not social acceptable. All well, I pull it together for the few students in the morning and I take a large breath and regroup.
